   "body" : "<!-- Describe the issue -->\r\n[bloom.cpp](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/4cef8e05938e55d2d1bb3c36642aa294fb63b6e2/src/bloom.cpp#L122-L165)\r\n[merkleblock.cpp](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/78dae8caccd82cfbfd76557f1fb7d7557c7b5edb/src/merkleblock.cpp#L28)\r\nAccording to these 2 files, MerkleBlock checks BIP37 bloom filter match without reordering transactions. I assume this brings a result that it miss a tx which is supposed to be matched if it meets the following conditions.\r\n\r\n- a block contains descendant transactions using existing filter's outpoint\r\n- child tx comes before its parent\r\n\r\nIf the filter has `BLOOM_UPDATE_ALL` or `BLOOM_UPDATE_P2PUBKEY_ONLY`, It also fails BloomFilter auto updating.\r\n\r\nI think it should re-order txs to parent comes before childrens before the process of merkle block filter match\r\n",
